<br>
Skalds and paladins are really the 2 classes which should be compared.  It is clear that they are the offensive and defensive variants of the same chanting class to come off the mythic drawing board.  Wardens are in the same line too, they got bubble, skalds got run speed, paladins got nothing since there are so many alb classes to spread the abilities out on.  Wardens being the &quot;magical&quot; version of the chanting melee have strayed so far from the initial concept it's not longer useful to directly compare them, so now it's just paladin vs skald, defensive vs offensive.<br>
<br>
